OnePlus has launched its new OnePlus 7 Pro smartphone, which boasts a high refresh-rate display and a retractable front-facing camera. The device features a completely bezel-less AMOLED display with a refresh rate of 90Hz and an in-screen optical fingerprint sensor. OnePlus has implemented a 6MP front camera which pops out of the top of the phoneâ€™s chassis when activated and retracts back into the device when not in use. A triple-lens 48MP camera is placed on the rear of the OnePlus 7 Pro, featuring up to 3x optical zoom and an ultra-wide angle lens. The OnePlus 7 Pro is priced from $669 and will be available in three models: The device will begin shipping internationally on 17 May 2019. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-306222" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-1.jpg" alt="OnePlus 7 Pro 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-1-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-1-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-306224" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-2.jpg" alt="OnePlus 7 Pro 2" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-2.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-2-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-2-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-306226" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/OnePlus-7-Pro-3.jpg" alt="OnePlus 7